{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}} {{multiple issues| {{expand German|topic=transport|otherarticle=Thai-Airways-Flug 231|date=March 2017}} {{one source|date=August 2013}} {{refimprove|date=August 2013}} }}
{{Infobox Aircraft occurrence |name = Thai Airways Flight 231 |occurrence_type = Accident |image = Thai Airways Hawker Siddeley HS-748 Green-2.jpg |caption = The aircraft involved in the accident at [[Chiang Mai Airport]] in 1976. |image_size = 251 px |alt = |date = 27 April 1980 |type = Pilot error in thunderstorm |site = 15 km north east of [[Bangkok]], Thailand |aircraft_type = [[Hawker Siddeley HS 748]] |operator = [[Thai Airways Company|Thai Airways]] |tail_number = HS-THB |origin = [[Khon Kaen Airport]], Thailand |destination = [[Don Mueang International Airport]], [[Bangkok]], Thailand |passengers = 49 |captain = |copilot = |crew = 4 |injuries = 9 |fatalities = 44 |survivors = 9 }}
'''[[Thai Airways Company|Thai Airways]] Flight 231''' crashed on 27 April 1980. The [[Hawker Siddeley HS 748]], registration HS-THB, [[Stall (fluid mechanics)|stalled]] and crashed after entering a [[thunderstorm]] on approach to [[Bangkok]]. The accident killed 44 out of 53 passengers and crew on board Flight 231.
==Accident== The flight took off from [[Khon Kaen Airport]] headed to [[Don Mueang International Airport]] in [[Bangkok]], Thailand. After about 40 minutes Flight 231 was on approach to the airport and planned to land on runway 21R. It entered an area of rain which turned out to be a severe thunderstorm at 1500 feet. About a minute after entering the storm a [[downdraft]] struck the plane which caused the nose to go up and the plane to [[Stall (fluid mechanics)|stall]]. The aircraft then went into a nose dive which the pilot tried to pull the aircraft out of. The Hawker then slightly banked to the right and was almost out of the dive when the aircraft crashed into the ground. The wreck of [[Hawker Siddeley HS 748]] then slid for 510 feet and broke up at 06:55. The accident killed 44 of the passengers and crew, 9 people were injured in the crash.
