{{Infobox dam | name = Uludere Dam | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Turkey | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|37|25|31.65|N|42|48|22.63|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Turkey | location = [[Uludere]], [[Şırnak Province]] | purpose = Water supply, military | status =UC | construction_began = 2008 | opening = | demolished = | cost = US$65,920,000 ([[Turkish lira|TL]]103,000,000) (Combined cost with [[Balli Dam]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Uludere Dam construction tender|url=http://www.dgmarket.com/tenders/adminShowBuyer.do~buyerId=1501335|publisher=DGMarkets|accessdate=3 August 2013|year=2008}}</ref> | owner = [[State Hydraulic Works]] | dam_type = Gravity, [[roller-compacted concrete]] | dam_height = {{Convert|55.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_height_foundation= | dam_length ={{Convert|431|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_width_crest = {{Convert|8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = {{Convert|35000|m3|cuyd|0|abbr=on}} | dam_elevation_crest ={{Convert|913|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_crosses = [[Ortasu River]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = Overflow | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|20100000|m3|acre.ft|0|abbr=on}} | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = {{Convert|196.4|km2|mi2|0|abbr=on}} | res_surface = | res_elevation ={{Convert|908.49|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | res_max_depth = | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = 2 (planned) | plant_capacity = 3.5 MW (planned)<ref name=KONNN/> | plant_annual_gen = | website = | extra = }} The '''Uludere Dam''' is a [[gravity dam]] under construction on the [[Ortasu River]] (a tributary of the [[Hezil River]]) in [[Uludere]] district of [[Şırnak Province]], southeast [[Turkey]]. Under contract from Turkey's [[State Hydraulic Works]], Hidrokon began construction on the dam in 2008 and a completion date has not been announced.<ref name=KONNN>{{cite web|title=ŞIRNAK ULUDERE DAM AND HEPP|url=http://www.hidrokonmuhendislik.com.tr/tr/14/anIIcat_3/8/anIIitm_3/33|publisher=Hidrokon|accessdate=2 August 2013|language=Turkish}}</ref>
The reported purpose of the dam is water storage and it can also support a 3.5 MW [[hydroelectric]] power station in the future.<ref>{{cite web|title=DSI 10 REGIONAL OFFICE - Diyarbakir|url=http://www2.dsi.gov.tr/bolge/dsi10/sirnak.htm|publisher=State Hydraulic Works|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish}}</ref> Another purpose of the dam which has been widely reported in the Turkish press is to reduce the freedom of movement of [[Kurdistan Workers' Party]] (PKK) militants. Blocking and flooding valleys in close proximity to the Iraq–Turkey border is expected to help curb cross-border PKK smuggling and deny caves in which ammunition can be stored. A total of 11 dams along the border; seven in Şırnak Province and four in [[Hakkâri Province]] were implemented for this purpose. In Şırnak they are the [[Silopi Dam|Silopi]] and [[Şırnak Dam]]s downstream of the Uludere Dam and the [[Balli Dam|Balli]], [[Kavşaktepe Dam|Kavşaktepe]], [[Musatepe Dam|Musatepe]] and [[Çetintepe Dam]]s upstream on the Ortasu River. In Hakkari are the Gölgeliyamaç (since cancelled) and [[Çocuktepe Dam]]s on the Güzeldere River and the [[Aslandağ Dam|Aslandağ]] and [[Beyyurdu Dam]]s on the Bembo River.<ref>{{cite web|title=Terror Down|url=http://www.posta.com.tr/turkiye/HaberDetay/Teror-bogulacak.htm?ArticleID=136637|publisher=Posta|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=24 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Planned to be completed in the second dam on the border against the PKK|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/19088520.asp|publisher=Hurriyet|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=26 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dams Prevent Smuggling at the Border|url=http://www.aktifhaber.com/sinirdaki-barajlar-kacakciligi-onleyecek-780919h.htm|publisher=Aktif Haber|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=5 May 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510001959/http://www.aktifhaber.com/sinirdaki-barajlar-kacakciligi-onleyecek-780919h.htm|archivedate=10 May 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Water retention dams began operation against PKK|url=http://www.cnnturk.com/2012/turkiye/08/23/pkkya.karsi.yapilan.barajlarda.su.tutma.islemi.basladi/674002.0/index.html|publisher=CNNTurk|accessdate=2 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=23 August 2012}}</ref>
