'''WindMade''' is a global (Brussel's based) consumer label for companies, events and products using [[wind power]] in their operations or production. It is aimed at promoting wind power and is guided by a Technical Advisory Board, which includes various scientists, and third-party auditors. The organization is a non-profit NGO established by seven Founding Partners: [[United Nations Global Compact]], [[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF]], [[Global Wind Energy Council]], [[LEGO Group]], PricewaterhouseCoopers ([[PwC]]), [[Bloomberg L.P.]] and [[Vestas Wind Systems]].<ref>Hilda Toonen and Han Lindeboom, [https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268514673_Dark_green_electricity_comes_from_the_sea_Capitalizing_on_ecological_merits_of_offshore_wind_power Dark green electricity comes from the sea], ''Renewable and Sustainable Energy Reviews'', (42) 2015.</ref>
